---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="LM Studio Setup - LrGeniusAI">
  <section class="lmstudio-setup-section">
    <h1>LM Studio Setup Instructions</h1>

    <h3>Download and Install LM Studio</h3>
    <p>Download and run the installer: <a href="https://lmstudio.ai/download" target="_blank">Here</a></p>

    <h3>Setup LM Studio for use with LrGeniusAI</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Start LM Studio</li>
        <li>Go to the Developer Tab</li>
        <li><b>Set status to: running</b></li>
        <li>In the Server Settings: <b>Activate Just-In-Time Model Loading</b></li>
    </ul>
    <img src="/images/lmstudio-settings.png" class="image-w-shadow">

    <h3>Pull an AI model</h3>
    <p><b>Go to the Discover Tab</b>: Search and download the AI model(s) you want to use. Recommended are:
    <ul>
        <li>google/gemma3-4b - Google's open source model</li>
        <li>google/gemma3-12b - Bigger version of Google's open source modelâ€š</li>
        <li>google/gemma3n-e4b - Reduced size (faster) version of gemma3:4b (macOS only, at the moment)</li>
        <li>qwen/qwen3-vl-4b - The current vision model from Alibaba</li>
        <li>qwen/qwen3-vl-8b - Bigger size of qwen3-vl-4b</li>
    </ul>
    There are different sizes for each model (4b, 8b, 12b). For optimal performance and results: Use the biggest model which offers <b>"Full GPU offload possible"</b>. Bigger means more intelligent, but requires more hardware resources.</p>

    <h3>macOS</h3>
    <p>If you are running LM Studio on macOS you should models with <b>MLX</b> format. Those models are optimized for Apple Silicon and offer better performance.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>


<style>
  .lmstudio-setup-section {
